===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Dorris had a population of 860. The population density was {{convert|1,225.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Dorris was 495 (57.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (0.3%) [[African Americans|African American]], 15 (1.7%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 18 (2.1%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 182 (21.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 147 (17.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 339 persons (39.4%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Dorris city, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0619584 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 318 households, out of which 109 (34.3%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 139 (43.7%) were married-couple households, 26 (8.2%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 90 (28.3%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 63 (19.8%) had a male householder with no partner present. 81 households (25.5%) were one person, and 43 (13.5%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.7.<ref name=DP1/> There were 207 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (65.1% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Dorris city, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0619584 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 19, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 236 people (27.4%) under the age of 18, 57 people (6.6%) aged 18 to 24, 208 people (24.2%) aged 25 to 44, 206 people (24.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 153 people (17.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 36.9{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 100.9 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 365 housing units at an average density of {{convert|519.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 318 (87.1%) were occupied. Of these, 203 (63.8%) were owner-occupied, and 115 (36.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
[[File:Dorris, CA mural.jpeg|thumb|250px|Mural on the Fire Department campus in Dorris.]]
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], Dorris had a population of 939. The population density was {{convert|1,307.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup was 764 (81.4%) White, 19 (2.0%) African American, 18 (1.9%) Native American, 5 (0.5%) Asian, 8 (0.9%) Pacific Islander, 77 (8.2%) from other races, and 48 (5.1%) from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race numbered 197 people (21.0%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0619584|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715024508/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0619584|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Dorris city|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The entire population lived in households; no one lived in non-institutionalized group quarters or was institutionalized.

There were 364 households, 125 (34.3%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 171 (47.0%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 47 (12.9%) had a female householder with no husband present, 23 (6.3%) had a male householder with no wife present. There were 33 (9.1%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (0.3%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 106 households (29.1%) were one person and 44 (12.1%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.58. There were 241 families (66.2% of households); the average family size was 3.15.

The age distribution was 240 people (25.6%) under the age of 18, 91 people (9.7%) aged 18 to 24, 216 people (23.0%) aged 25 to 44, 256 people (27.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 136 people (14.5%) who were 65 or older. The median age was 38.2 years. For every 100 females, there were 102.4 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 94.2 males.

There were 414 housing units at an average density of 576.5 per square mile. 248 (68.1%) of the occupied units were owner-occupied and 116 (31.9%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 3.9%; the rental vacancy rate was 7.2%. 584 people (62.2% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 355 people (37.8%) lived in rental housing units.

